GitHub Desktop Installation
Date
July 7, 2026

Objective
Install GitHub Desktop to manage Git repositories locally, organize cybersecurity documentation, and synchronize projects with GitHub.

Why GitHub Desktop?
GitHub Desktop provides a user-friendly interface for Git version control, making it easier to create repositories, organize files and folders, track changes, commit updates, and push projects to GitHub without relying on command-line Git. 
It will serve as the primary tool for maintaining my cybersecurity portfolio and documenting my learning journey.

Installation
Operating System:
macOS

Version:
Apple Silicon M2 MacBook Air

Installation Method:
Downloaded and installed GitHub Desktop from the official GitHub website.

Verification:
Successfully launched GitHub Desktop.
Signed in to my GitHub account.
Cloned my existing repository to my local machine.
Reorganized repository folders locally.
Committed changes and successfully pushed updates to GitHub.

Reflection:
Today I learned how GitHub Desktop simplifies repository management by allowing files and folders to be organized locally while automatically tracking changes through Git. 
This workflow is significantly more efficient than managing repositories through the GitHub website alone.
This will be my primary method for maintaining and expanding my cybersecurity portfolio as I complete labs, learning paths, and home lab projects.
